{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments"]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"UnfairLock","symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnfairLock","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"Instruments"}],"roleHeading":"Class","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"UnfairLock","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:11Instruments10UnfairLockC","role":"symbol"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/init()"],"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"title":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/lock()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/try()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/unlock()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/withLock(_:)"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/NSLocking-Implementations"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock"},"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"List of Tools","anchor":"List-of-Tools","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/BytesConstructibleNumber","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/Endianness","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/DebounceFunction","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/DebounceFunctionConfiguration","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/HexStringDataDecoder","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/HexStringDataDecoderError","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/LLDB","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/WeakShared","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/Pointer","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/SecureRandom","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/SecureRandomError","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/Timer","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/LineByLineReader","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/LinewiseReader","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/DelegatePool"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/objc(pl)NSLocking","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/s16SendableMetatypeP"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnfairLock"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"UnfairLock is an appropriate lock for cases where simple and lightweight mutual exclusion is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"needed. It can be intrusively stored inline in a data structure without needing a separate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allocation, reducing memory consumption and cost of indirection. For situations where something","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"more sophisticated like condition waits or FIFO ordering is needed, use appropriate higher level","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"APIs such as those from the pthread or dispatch subsystems."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The values stored in the lock should be considered opaque and implementation defined, they","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"contain thread ownership information that the system may use to attempt to resolve priority"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"inversions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock must be unlocked from the same thread that locked it, attempts to unlock from a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"different thread will cause an assertion aborting the process."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This lock must not be accessed from multiple processes or threads via shared or multiply-mapped","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"memory, because the lock implementation relies on the address of the lock value and identity of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the owning process."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The name ‘unfair’ indicates that there is no attempt at enforcing acquisition fairness, e.g. an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unlocker can potentially immediately reacquire the lock before a woken up waiter gets an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"opportunity to attempt to acquire the lock. This is often advantageous for performance reasons,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but also makes starvation of waiters a possibility."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock is suitable as a drop-in replacement for the deprecated OSSpinLock, providing much"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"better behavior under contention."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/instruments\/unfairlock"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Low-level lock that allows waiters to block efficiently on contention."}],"references":{"doc://instruments.Instruments/documentation/Instruments/UnfairLock/NSLocking-Implementations":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/instruments\/unfairlock\/nslocking-implementations","title":"NSLocking Implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/NSLocking-Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://instruments.Instruments/documentation/Instruments/UnfairLock/withLock(_:)":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/instruments\/unfairlock\/withlock(_:)","title":"withLock(_:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/withLock(_:)","abstract":[{"text":"Executes given code by wrapping it with ","type":"text"},{"code":"lock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"unlock()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" methods.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"withLock","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Result","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(() ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Result","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Instruments10UnfairLockC04withC0yxxyKXEKlF6ResultL_xmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"rethrows","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Result","preciseIdentifier":"s:11Instruments10UnfairLockC04withC0yxxyKXEKlF6ResultL_xmfp","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://instruments.Instruments/documentation/Instruments/HexStringDataDecoder":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/instruments\/hexstringdatadecoder","title":"HexStringDataDecoder","identifier":"doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/HexStringDataDecoder","abstract":[{"text":"A de